Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Pop a large #saucepan of water onto boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Slice the @potatoes{450%g} into ½ cm discs (no need to peel). Add to the boiling water and simmer gently until the potatoes have softened but are not cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Roughly chop the @dill{2%sprigs} (stalks and all). When the potatoes are cooked, drain into a #colander and allow to steam for a couple of minutes.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #saucepan on medium heat. Add the shallot with a pinch of @salt{} and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once the potatoes are cooked, drain them in a colander, return to the saucepan with the @soured cream{150%g}, the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}, @water{2%tbsp} and half the dill. Add the cooked shallot and plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Gently mix and transfer into a #baking dish{}. Bake on the top shelf of your #oven until bubbling and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Put the @white wine vinegar{24%ml}, @sugar{1.5%tbsp}, @water{2%tbsp} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a small #saucepan over medium heat. Cook until the sugar and salt have dissolved, ~{1-2%minutes}. Trim the @cucumber{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the cucumber. Stop when you get to the seeds. Pop the cucumber into a #mixing bowl{} and pour over the vinegar mixture, add the remaining dill and mix well. Set aside while you cook the salmon.

About ~{15%minutes} before the gratin is done, mix the @wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp} and @honey{15%g} with a drizzle of @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pop the @salmon fillets{2} on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{} and spoon the mustard mixture over, spreading with the back of a #spoon to evenly cover the salmon. Bake on the middle shelf of your #oven for ~{12-14%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the gratin is done, leave to stand for ~{5%minutes} before serving. Pour off any excess liquid from the cucumber.

Divide the salmon between plates with the pickled cucumber and potato gratin alongside. Enjoy!